le=\"Henry Draper Catalogue\" href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Henry_Draper_Catalogue\">HD<\/a> 178428<\/td><td><a title=\"Sagitta\" href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Sagitta\">Sagitta<\/a><\/td><td><span style=\"display: none;\">1999-06-30<\/span>June 30, 1999<\/td><td><span style=\"display: none;\">2067-10<\/span>October 2067<\/td><td><a title=\"Cosmic Call\" href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Cosmic_Call\">Cosmic Call<\/a> 1<\/td><\/tr><tr align=\"center\"><td><a title=\"16 Cygni\" href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/16_Cygni\">16 Cyg A<\/a><\/td><td><a title=\"Henry Draper Catalogue\" href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Henry_Draper_Catalogue\">HD<\/a> 186408<\/td><td><a title=\"Cygnus (constellation)\" href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Cygnus_(constellation)\">Cygnus<\/a><\/td><td><span style=\"display: none;\">1999-05-24<\/span>May 24, 1999<\/td><td><span style=\"display: none;\">2069-11<\/span>November 2069<\/td><td><a title=\"Cosmic Call\" href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Cosmic_Call\">Cosmic Call<\/a> 1<\/td><\/tr><tr align=\"center\"><td><\/td><td><a title=\"Henry Draper Catalogue\" href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Henry_Draper_Catalogue\">HD<\/a> 197076<\/td><td><a title=\"Delphinus\" href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Delphinus\">Delphinus<\/a><\/td><td><span style=\"display: none;\">2000-08-29<\/span>August 29, 2001<\/td><td><span style=\"display: none;\">2070-02<\/span>February 2070<\/td><td><a title=\"Teen Age Message\" href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Teen_Age_Message\">Teen Age Message<\/a><\/td><\/tr><tr align=\"center\"><td><a title=\"Messier 13\" href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Messier_13\">Messier 13<\/a><\/td><td>NGC 6205<\/td><td><a title=\"Hercules (constellation)\" href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Hercules_(constellation)\">Hercules<\/a><\/td><td><span style=\"display: none;\">1974-11-16<\/span>November 16, 1974<\/td><td>approx. 25974<\/td><td><a class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Arecibo Message\" href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Arecibo_Message\">Arecibo Message<\/a><\/td><\/tr><\/tbody><\/table>\r\n\r\nI personally take the stance that active SETI is completely reckless and anyone doing this is a danger to the entire human race. If anything, we should be trying to mask our presence in the universe. Whatever alien intelligence we come across may well be hostile (e.g. a <a  href=\"https:\/\/secure.wikimedia.org\/wikipedia\/en\/wiki\/Berserker_probe#Berserkers\">berserker probe<\/a>). The technology that they posses is also likely to be far more advanced than that of our own. Our solar system has been about for billions of years and our galaxy for much longer. There has been plenty of time for alien intelligence to grow exponenitially beyond anything we can imagine - especially if <a href=\"https:\/\/secure.wikimedia.org\/wikipedia\/en\/wiki\/Predictions_made_by_Ray_Kurzweil#The_Singularity_is_Near_.282005.29\">Kurzweil's predictions<\/a> are anything to go by.\r\n\r\nFinally, if I simply can't win the arguement that Active SETI is a tremendous gamble then active SETI should be done from a neutral location, not our home planet...","title":"Active SETI? - no thanks","status":"publish","name":"how-far-have-we-shouted","type":"","tags":["Aliens","SETI","Berserker Probe"],"categories":["Astrothoughts"],"comments":[{"author":"Vas","authorEmail":"VasVadum@Gmail.com","authorURL":"","authorIP":"66.143.206.9","timestamp":"2011-06-20 13:25:21","timestampGMT":"2011-06-20 12:25:21","comment":"For that last bit, do you think that aliens will be hostile just because of all the dumb movies?  I don't think aliens would find a jumbled mess of signals and come all the way out to us just to launch an attack.  Besides that by the times mentioned above, I bet we'd have better ways of sending signals and better defenses.\r\n\r\nI assume that many alien races could be along the same evolutionary track as us so we'd probably be looking at more human like people with same inside body chemistry with probably slightly different appearances.  We'd all probably get along fine aside from the heavily religious people.","browser":"Mozilla\/5.0 (Windows NT 6.1; rv:2.0.1) Gecko\/20100101 Firefox\/4.0.1"}]}